  "observations": [
    "Daily note for today is the default landing page — Φ entry-point is temporal, not hierarchical",
    "Every block carries a UUID and is addressable as first-class entity (((uuid))), not just pages",
    "Outliner with zoom-in: clicking a bullet replaces workspace with that block + descendants and adds a breadcrumb",
    "Bidirectional links auto-materialize: creating [[Page]] inside a block creates the page node and a backlink edge",
    "Linked References footer aggregates all blocks across all pages that mention current page title or its aliases",
    "Unlinked References footer surfaces plain-text mentions as candidates for explicit linking",
    "Block embed (( )) renders as live-mirror — edits propagate to all embed sites, distinct from one-shot copy",
    "Right sidebar acts as stacked workspace: shift-click opens additional page/block panes alongside main",
    "Inline DSL queries ({{query: ...}}) are stored as blocks and re-evaluated live — query is data, not view-config",
    "Attributes (Key:: Value inside block) double as searchable KV-rows and as table-pivot under Attributes/Key namespace",
    "TODO is just an attribute/tag pattern aggregated through the same query DSL — no dedicated task entity",
    "Multi-select across bullets enables group-actions (move, copy ref, color) — bulk-action-toolbar pattern",
    "Keyboard shortcuts dominate (Cmd-U quick-open, Cmd-Shift-9 search, Tab/Shift-Tab indent) — global-command-palette and keyboard-property-popover patterns are core, not optional",
    "Permissions are graph-scoped (graphOwner / editor / reader / public-viewer), not page-scoped",
    "Public graph is a visibility flag on Graph entity with custom URL — read-only mirror, not a separate copy",
    "Real-time multiplayer presence and per-block comments imply CRDT-style block model with author+timestamp on every block",
    "Plugins (roam/css, roam/js, SmartBlocks) live as code inside special pages — codebase is part of the graph itself",
    "Deep undo history (Cmd-Z) implies effect-log retention beyond session scope"
  ]
}